            "heading": "Six things people ask every week.",
            "intro": "<p>Click any question to expand the answer. If yours isn't here, jump to <a href=\"#contact\">contact</a> at the bottom.</p>",
            "q_1": "My ferment isn't bubbling on Day 2. Did I do something wrong?",
            "a_1": "<p>Probably not — visible bubbling depends on temperature and ingredient sugar content. At 22–25°C, expect bubbles by Day 2–3 in vegetable ferments and Day 1 in kanji. Below 18°C, fermentation slows by 50%.</p><p>If it's still flat by Day 4, send us a photo on WhatsApp. We can usually diagnose from a picture.</p>",
            "q_2": "There's white film on the surface of my ferment. Is it mould?",
            "a_2": "<p>Almost always it's <strong>kahm yeast</strong> — a harmless surface film that forms when oxygen reaches the brine. Skim it off with a clean spoon and continue. Your ferment is fine.</p><p>True mould is fuzzy and coloured (blue/green/black/pink). If you see that, throw the batch out and message us — we'll send a free replacement.</p>",
            "q_3": "Can children have probiotic ferments?",
            "a_3": "<p>Yes — kanji, dahi, kefir, and kimchi (mild) are safe and healthy for children over 1 year. Start with small portions (1–2 tbsp) and work up.</p><p>Avoid: anything with raw honey for under-1-year-olds (botulism risk, unrelated to fermentation).</p>",
            "q_4": "How long does my fermented batch last in the fridge?",
            "a_4": "<p>Once refrigerated and the pH is below 4.0:</p><p>• <strong>Vegetable ferments</strong> (achaar, sauerkraut, kimchi): 2–6 months<br>• <strong>Kanji</strong>: 4–6 weeks<br>• <strong>Yogurt/kefir</strong>: 7–10 days<br>• <strong>Sourdough discard</strong>: 3 weeks</p><p>The flavour will keep developing — not a sign of spoilage.</p>",
            "q_5": "Can I use iodised salt?",
            "a_5": "<p><strong>No.</strong> Iodine kills lactic acid bacteria. Use sea salt, rock salt, or any non-iodised salt. The kits ship with the right salt; if you're refilling, check the label.</p>",
            "q_6": "Where do I find the recipe for kit X?",
            "a_6": "<p>Every kit ships with a printed recipe card. Digital copies live at <a href=\"/pages/recipes\">/pages/recipes</a>. If yours is missing or unclear, message us on WhatsApp with the kit name and we'll send a PDF in 30 seconds.</p>"
